title: [BUG] mlflow inference tensorflow inception model giving error
body:
Hi All ,

I am trying to serve a already saved tensorflow  inception model using the below code :
model_path = "/Users/i311157/Downloads/data/inception"
```
mlflow.tensorflow.save_model(tf_saved_model_dir=model_path, tf_meta_graph_tags=[tag_constants.SERVING],
                             tf_signature_def_key="predict_images",
                             path="savedmodel",
                            conda_env ="/Users/i311157/PycharmProjects/mlflow-tf/conda.yaml"

```

I start serving the model from cli using below command :

mlflow models serve --model-uri <MODEL-PATH-URL> -p 54321


Once the https server is up I try to do inference using the below :

```
curl -X POST \
  http://127.0.0.1:54321/invocations \
  -H 'Accept: */*' \
  -H 'Accept-Encoding: gzip, deflate' \
  -H 'Cache-Control: no-cache' \
  -H 'Connection: keep-alive' \
  -H 'Content-Length: 20552' \
  -H 'Content-Type: application/json' \
  -H 'Host: 127.0.0.1:54321' \
  -H 'Postman-Token: 442368b4-808a-4c87-a514-0058853226be,4faba288-a91f-4f23-9714-94ffaf72cea1' \
  -H 'User-Agent: PostmanRuntime/7.15.2' \
  -H 'cache-control: no-cache' \
  -H 'format: pandas-split' \
  -d '{"columns":["images"],"index":[0],"data":[""}}
'
```
But i am getting the below error :
```
{
      ret = Operation(c_op, self)\n  File \"/Users/i311157/PycharmProjects/mlf-python-grpc-model-server/venv/lib/python3.6/site-packages/tensorflow/python/framework/ops.py\", line 1768, in __init__\n    self._traceback = tf_stack.extract_stack()\n\nInvalidArgumentError (see above for traceback): Expected image (JPEG, PNG, or GIF), got unknown format starting with 'image/jpeg;base6'\n\t [[{{node map/while/DecodeJpeg}} = DecodeJpeg[acceptable_fraction=1, channels=3, dct_method=\"\", fancy_upscaling=true, ratio=1, try_recover_truncated=false, _device=\"/job:localhost/replica:0/task:0/device:CPU:0\"](map/while/TensorArrayReadV3)]]\n\n"
```


It gives me unknown format error but the test image is jpeg file still it gives the above error .

But when i try directly from the code like the below i get the prediction result:
```
tf_graph = tf.Graph()
tf_sess = tf.Session(graph=tf_graph)
signature_def =tensorflow.load_model("/Users/i311157/PycharmProjects/mlflow-tf/mlruns/0/8167e43b47474b88b81a9069d1d45110/artifacts/model",tf_sess=tf_sess)
model = _tensorflow(tf_sess=tf_sess, tf_graph=tf_graph, signature_def=signature_def)
image_data = tf.gfile.GFile("/Users/i311157/PycharmProjects/mlflow-tf/data/testmlflow.jpeg", 'rb').read()                    columns=["images"])
df = pd.DataFrame(
    data=[image_data],
    columns=["images"])
df.to_csv("test1.csv")
json_data=df.to_json(orient="split")
predict_df = model.predict(df)

   scores                                 classes
0  10.083101         b'lycaenid, lycaenid butterfly'
1   7.066910           b'ringlet, ringlet butterfly'
2   4.377772                    b'cabbage butterfly'
3   3.555962  b'sulphur butterfly, sulfur butterfly'
4   2.427257                              b'admiral'
```
So I am not sure what is wrong when i call http endpoint .
When i directly send the predict i send the raw jpeg image but when i call i cannot do that so i send the b64 encoded.
Kindly please help.

Many Thanks.
PLease let me know for any other information.
